name: InternalInjuryOfChestAbdomenAndPelvis
title: Internal injury of chest, abdomen, and pelvis
description: OP-11 is the measure ID associated with the codes.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains ICD-9 codes associated with injuries to the abdomen, lower back, lumbar spine, pelvis, and external genitals.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have injuries to the abdomen, lower back, lumbar spine, pelvis, and external genitals.),(Inclusion Criteria: ICD-9 codes associated with injuries to the abdomen, lower back, lumbar spine, pelvis, and external genitals are included in this value set.),(Exclusion Criteria: Values that are not related to injuries to the abdomen, lower back, lumbar spine, pelvis, and external genitals, or those captured in systems other than ICD-9, are excluded from the value set.)
